<section style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><section class="Powered-by-XIUMI V5" style="   box-sizing: border-box; " powered-by="xiumi.us"><section class="" style=" margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;  box-sizing: border-box; "><section class="" style="width: 2.5em; margin-left: auto; box-sizing: border-box;"><section style="width: 2.5em; border-top-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(158, 158, 158); box-sizing: border-box;"></section><section style="height: 1.4em; border-left-width: 1px; border-left-style: solid; border-left-color: rgb(158, 158, 158); margin-top: -0.5em; margin-left: 2em; box-sizing: border-box;"></section></section><section class="" style="padding-right: 0.5em; padding-left: 0.5em; box-sizing: border-box;"><section class="" style="padding: 10px; box-sizing: border-box;"><section class="Powered-by-XIUMI V5" style="   box-sizing: border-box; " powered-by="xiumi.us"><section class="" style=" margin-right: 0%; margin-left: 0%;  box-sizing: border-box; "><section class="" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(75, 101, 98); box-sizing: border-box;"><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">As the number of drug users continuously increasing with the implement of unhygienic injection, along with the other methods like sexual behavior without protection, more and more people are carrying the AIDS. However, unfair treatments towards people with HIV, including discrimination, violence, punitive laws, policies and practices, remain to be a serious issue all over the world. In order to find a proper solution to it, this winter, all delegates of United Nations Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (UNAIDS) are scheduled to gather together in HIT, discussing, debating and focusing on two key problems-How to defend the human rights of AIDS patients and how to get rid of the stigma?</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p></section></section></section></section></section><section class="" style="height: 1.4em; border-left-width: 1px; border-left-style: solid; border-left-color: rgb(158, 158, 158); margin-bottom: -0.5em; margin-left: 0.5em; box-sizing: border-box;"></section><section class="" style="width: 2.5em; border-top-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(158, 158, 158); box-sizing: border-box;"></section></section></section><section class="Powered-by-XIUMI V5" style="   box-sizing: border-box; " powered-by="xiumi.us"><section class="" style=" text-align: center; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;  box-sizing: border-box; "><img style="vertical-align: middle; box-sizing: border-box;" class="" data-ratio="0.751131221719457" data-w="442" src="http://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/lZxqO3dCoYgHJaoRzf7PBKxdKv0MOIGATPnYOp0kBDfEf4yYkBgI9VnlPR7ZLZIoiaeAGgPVZ1YhQKerpicXLibIg/0?wx_fmt=jpeg" data-type="jpeg"  /></section></section><section class="Powered-by-XIUMI V5" style="   box-sizing: border-box; " powered-by="xiumi.us"><section class="" style="   box-sizing: border-box; "><section class="" style="box-sizing: border-box;"><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br  /></strong></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box;">1.How to defend the human rights of AIDS patients?</strong></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Though the joint efforts by the international community, we are delighted to notice that the living environment of AIDS patients has taken a turn for the better and the sense of equality has become a universal value. People living with HIV and HIV/AIDS defenders have secured important victories, including access to medicines, law reform and so on. Nevertheless, the AIDS epidemic is still driven by human rights violations around the world, including discrimination, violence, punitive laws, policies and practices. Negative events are still reported across the globe.</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">So what can we do to broadcast the value of human rights to farther places? what sort of brand-new methods can we try to guarantee the AIDS patients being treated fairly?</span></p></section></section></section><section class="Powered-by-XIUMI V5" style="   box-sizing: border-box; " powered-by="xiumi.us"><section class="" style=" margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; padding-right: 3px; padding-left: 3px;  box-sizing: border-box; "><section class="" style="display: inline-block; width: 100%; vertical-align: top; margin-bottom: -0.65em; margin-top: 0.95em; box-sizing: border-box;"><section style="width: 100%; box-sizing: border-box;"><section style="border-top-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(160, 160, 160); width: 99.9%; float: left; box-sizing: border-box;"></section><section style="width: 6px; height: 6px; margin-top: -3px; border-radius: 100%; float: right; box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(160, 160, 160);"></section></section><section class="" style="display: inline-block; margin-top: -1em; vertical-align: top; padding: 3px 10px; box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(254, 255, 255);"><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p></section></section></section></section><section class="Powered-by-XIUMI V5" style="   box-sizing: border-box; " powered-by="xiumi.us"><section class="" style="   box-sizing: border-box; "><section class="" style="box-sizing: border-box;"><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box;">2.How to get rid of the stigma?</strong></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Even in such an era of information explosion, HIV/AIDS stigma is still deeply believed by a large part of popularity to some degree. The stigma has obviously become a barrier for HIV patient to fight for their legal rights, causing severe damage to them.</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">HIV/AIDS stigma can be divided into the following three categories:</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">I.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Instrumental AIDS stigma—a reflection of the fear and apprehension that are likely to be associated with any deadly and transmissible illness.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">II.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Symbolic AIDS stigma—the use of HIV/AIDS to express attitudes toward the social groups or lifestyles perceived to be associated with the disease.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">III.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Courtesy AIDS stigma—stigmatization of people connected to the issue of HIV/AIDS or HIV-positive people.</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Based on these categories, how can we have a person believing in scientific results but these three types of stigma in an efficient way?</span></p></section></section></section><section class="Powered-by-XIUMI V5" style="   box-sizing: border-box; " powered-by="xiumi.us"><section class="" style=" margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; padding-right: 3px; padding-left: 3px;  box-sizing: border-box; "><section class="" style="display: inline-block; width: 100%; vertical-align: top; margin-bottom: -0.65em; margin-top: 0.95em; box-sizing: border-box;"><section style="width: 100%; box-sizing: border-box;"><section style="border-top-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(160, 160, 160); width: 99.9%; float: left; box-sizing: border-box;"></section><section style="width: 6px; height: 6px; margin-top: -3px; border-radius: 100%; float: right; box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(160, 160, 160);"></section></section><section class="" style="display: inline-block; margin-top: -1em; vertical-align: top; padding: 3px 10px; box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(254, 255, 255);"><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p></section></section></section></section><section class="Powered-by-XIUMI V5" style="   box-sizing: border-box; " powered-by="xiumi.us"><section class="" style="   box-sizing: border-box; "><section class="" style="box-sizing: border-box;"><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Human beings have been fighting with HIV for over 30 years. It is certain that HIV can be ranked one of the most intractable virus. It must be a heart-broken thing for a person to become a HIV patient. In this case, if he can renew hope of life, what should be showed to him is never the evil-minded words but applause. As the participants of UNAIDS, all delegates will shoulder their responsibility and spare no effort to seek for the solution.</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"  /></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Looking forward to their performance!</span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; text-align: right;"><span style="color: rgb(136, 136, 136); font-family: 宋体; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6;"></span></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; text-align: right;"><span style="color: rgb(136, 136, 136); font-family: 宋体; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6;">周芳桐 姚玮婷 张书宁 王若颖 周卓|审核</span><br  /></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; text-align: right;"><span style="color: rgb(136, 136, 136); font-size: 12px;">子明|编辑&nbsp;</span></p></section></section></section><sectio